# 
Leno Coding Standards

## General Dart Guidelines

### Code Style
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Max line length: 80 characters (flexible for readability)
- Use trailing commas for better formatting
- Follow official Dart style guide

### Naming Conventions
```dart
// Classes: PascalCase
class PetRepository {}

// Files: snake_case
// pet_repository.dart

// Variables/functions: camelCase
String userName = 'Alex';
void loadUserData() {}

// Constants: lowerCamelCase
const String apiBaseUrl = 'https://api.example.com';

// Private members: prefix with underscore
String _privateField;
void _privateMethod() {}
```

### Comments
```dart
// Use // for single-line comments
// Explain WHY, not WHAT

/// Use /// for documentation comments
/// This function calculates the pet's age in years
String calculateAge(DateTime birthday) {
  // Implementation
}

// TODO: Add error handling
// FIXME: This breaks on leap years
```

## Flutter-Specific Guidelines

### Widget Structure
```dart
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  // 1. Constructor parameters (final fields)
  final String title;
  final VoidCallback? onTap;

  // 2. Constructor
  const MyWidget({
    Key? key,
    required this.title,
    this.onTap,
  }) : super(key: key);

  // 3. Build method
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container(
      // Widget tree
    );
  }

  // 4. Private helper methods
  void _handleTap() {
    onTap?.call();
  }
}
```

### StatefulWidget Pattern
```dart
class MyStatefulWidget extends StatefulWidget {
  final String initialValue;

  const MyStatefulWidget({
    Key? key,
    required this.initialValue,
  }) : super(key: key);

  @override
  State<MyStatefulWidget> createState() => _MyStatefulWidgetState();
}

class _MyStatefulWidgetState extends State<MyStatefulWidget> {
  // 1. State variables
  late String _currentValue;
  bool _isLoading = false;

  // 2. Lifecycle methods
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _currentValue = widget.initialValue;
    _loadData();
  }

  @override
  void dispose() {
    // Clean up controllers, listeners
    super.dispose();
  }

  // 3. Build method
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container();
  }

  // 4. Private methods
  Future<void> _loadData() async {
    setState(() {
      _isLoading = true;
    });
    // Load data
    setState(() {
      _isLoading = false;
    });
  }
}
```

### BuildContext Usage
```dart
// Access theme
final theme = Theme.of(context);
final isDark = theme.brightness == Brightness.dark;

// Access MediaQuery
final size = MediaQuery.of(context).size;
final padding = MediaQuery.of(context).padding;

// Navigation
Navigator.push(context, MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => NewScreen()));
Navigator.pop(context);
Navigator.pop(context, result);
```

## State Management with setState

### Simple State Updates
```dart
void _updateValue(String newValue) {
  setState(() {
    _currentValue = newValue;
  });
}
```

### Async Operations
```dart
Future<void> _loadData() async {
  setState(() {
    _isLoading = true;
  });

  try {
    final data = await repository.fetchData();
    setState(() {
      _data = data;
      _isLoading = false;
    });
  } catch (e) {
    setState(() {
      _error = e.toString();
      _isLoading = false;
    });
  }
}
```

### Conditional setState
```dart
void _updateIfMounted(VoidCallback fn) {
  if (mounted) {
    setState(fn);
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

### Try-Catch Pattern
```dart
Future<void> _saveData() async {
  try {
    await repository.save(data);
    _showSuccessMessage();
  } catch (e) {
    _showErrorMessage(e.toString());
  }
}
```

### Null Safety
```dart
// Use ? for nullable types
String? optionalValue;

// Use ?? for default values
String displayName = user.name ?? 'Unknown';

// Use ?. for safe navigation
int? length = user.pets?.length;

// Use ! only when absolutely certain
String name = user.name!; // Avoid if possible
```

## UI Best Practices

### Responsive Design
```dart
// Use MediaQuery for responsive sizing
final screenWidth = MediaQuery.of(context).size.width;
final isTablet = screenWidth > 600;

// Use LayoutBuilder for adaptive layouts
LayoutBuilder(
  builder: (context, constraints) {
    if (constraints.maxWidth > 600) {
      return TabletLayout();
    }
    return MobileLayout();
  },
)
```

### Theme Access
```dart
// Access custom colors
final theme = Theme.of(context);
final primaryColor = theme.primaryColor;
final textColor = theme.textTheme.bodyLarge?.color;

// Use theme-aware colors
Container(
  color: theme.brightness == Brightness.dark
    ? AppConstants.darkGray
    : AppConstants.panelWhite,
)
```

### Spacing and Sizing
```dart
// Use SizedBox for spacing
SizedBox(height: 16),
SizedBox(width: 8),

// Use EdgeInsets for padding
Padding(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(16),
  child: child,
)

// Use consistent spacing
const double kSpacingSmall = 8.0;
const double kSpacingMedium = 16.0;
const double kSpacingLarge = 24.0;
```

## Performance Tips

### Const Constructors
```dart
// Use const when possible
const SizedBox(height: 16)
const Text('Static text')
const Icon(Icons.home)
```

### Avoid Rebuilds
```dart
// Extract static widgets
class _StaticHeader extends StatelessWidget {
  const _StaticHeader();
  
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Text('Header');
  }
}

// Use in parent
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return Column(
    children: [
      const _StaticHeader(), // Won't rebuild
      DynamicContent(data: _data),
    ],
  );
}
```

### ListView Performance
```dart
// Use ListView.builder for long lists
ListView.builder(
  itemCount: items.length,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) {
    return ItemWidget(item: items[index]);
  },
)

// Use ListView.separated for dividers
ListView.separated(
  itemCount: items.length,
  itemBuilder: (context, index) => ItemWidget(items[index]),
  separatorBuilder: (context, index) => Divider(),
)
```

## Testing Considerations

### Testable Code Structure
```dart
// Separate business logic from UI
class PetService {
  Future<List<Pet>> getPets() async {
    // Logic here
  }
}

// UI just calls service
class PetsScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  final PetService service;
  
  const PetsScreen({required this.service});
}
```

### Mock-Friendly Design
```dart
// Use abstract classes for repositories
abstract class PetRepository {
  Future<List<Pet>> getAll();
  Future<void> add(Pet pet);
}

// Concrete implementation
class PetRepositoryImpl implements PetRepository {
  @override
  Future<List<Pet>> getAll() async {
    // Implementation
  }
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Loading States
```dart
if (_isLoading) {
  return Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator());
}

if (_error != null) {
  return Center(child: Text('Error: $_error'));
}

return ContentWidget(data: _data);
```

### Empty States
```dart
if (_items.isEmpty) {
  return Center(
    child: Column(
      mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
      children: [
        Icon(Icons.inbox, size: 64, color: Colors.grey),
        SizedBox(height: 16),
        Text('No items yet'),
      ],
    ),
  );
}
```

### Dialogs
```dart
Future<bool?> _showConfirmDialog() async {
  return showDialog<bool>(
    context: context,
    builder: (context) => AlertDialog(
      title: Text('Confirm'),
      content: Text('Are you sure?'),
      actions: [
        TextButton(
          onPressed: () => Navigator.pop(context, false),
          child: Text('Cancel'),
        ),
        TextButton(
          onPressed: () => Navigator.pop(context, true),
          child: Text('Confirm'),
        ),
      ],
    ),
  );
}
```

## Avoid These Patterns

❌ **Don't use BuildContext after async gap without checking mounted**
```dart
// Bad
Future<void> _loadData() async {
  await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 1));
  Navigator.pop(context); // Context might be invalid
}

// Good
Future<void> _loadData() async {
  await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 1));
  if (mounted) {
    Navigator.pop(context);
  }
}
```

❌ **Don't call setState in build method**
```dart
// Bad
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  setState(() { /* ... */ }); // Never do this
  return Container();
}
```

❌ **Don't forget to dispose controllers**
```dart
// Bad
class _MyState extends State<MyWidget> {
  final _controller = TextEditingController();
  // No dispose method
}

// Good
class _MyState extends State<MyWidget> {
  final _controller = TextEditingController();
  
  @override
  void dispose() {
    _controller.dispose();
    super.dispose();
  }
}
```
